parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transfer case can cause a loss of power, vibration, and loud banging sounds, leading to a potential loss of control, accidents, and injuries. The failure can also result in damage to surrounding components, including the front driveshaft, fuel lines, brake lines, electrical wiring, and exhaust system.
The failure of the non-adjustable ball joints can cause uneven tire wear, leading to a potential blowout hazard, which can result in loss of control, accidents, and injuries.
symptoms: Uneven tire wear on the outside cord only

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the shifter cable can cause the vehicle to shift out of gear without warning, leading to loss of control, accidents, and injuries.
symptoms: Vehicle shifts out of gear and goes into neutral without warning

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel pump can cause the vehicle to shut off, leading to loss of control, accidents, and injuries.
symptoms: Fuse in the fuel pump overheats without warning

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the idler pulley belt can cause the steering to lose power and the air conditioning to lose its cooling capability, leading to loss of control, accidents, and injuries.
Sudden tire failure can lead to loss of vehicle control, accidents, and injuries, especially at high speeds.
The "death wobble" can cause loss of vehicle control, accidents, and injuries, especially at high speeds.
symptoms: difficulty maintaining control of the vehicle.
